Abe’s Liberal Democratic Party Prevails in Japan’s Local Elections
TOKYO—Prime Minister Shinzo Abe’s Liberal Democratic Party cruised to victory in Japan’s local elections Sunday, as voter turnout likely remained at record-low levels throughout the country.
Voting took place in 10 gubernatorial races and five mayoral elections in government-designated major cities as well as for assembly seats in 41 prefectures and 17 cities.